British Council under its “Managing Conflict in Nigeria (MCN)” has donated COVID-19 items to the Family Support Unit of the Nigeria Police Force (NPF) in three local government areas of Borno State. Speaking during the handover of the items yesterday at Police Headquarters Maiduguri, Borno State Team Leader of Managing Conflict in Nigeria, Aminu Buba, said that the intervention is aimed at strengthening mechanism to support the fight against sexual and gender-based violence in the state. Buba said the items would enhance family units in Maiduguri, Biu and Mafa Divisional Stations to support the fight against sexual and gender based violence in Borno State. “We are here to donate COVID-19 items for use in the three Family Support Units. We have supported in establishing one in the state, with the two others at Biu and Mafa Divisional Stations. We hope the items will add value to the services the police are providing to the people,” Buba said. Responding, Borno State commissioner of police, CP Abdu Umar thanked British Council for the gesture and said that the items will go a long way to aid process of investigation of sexual and gender based violence in the command. Umar assured that the command would make judicious use of the items and distribute them as specified by the British Council to achieve the desired goal.